Linear modeling and terminology






A generalized linear model states \(E[Y|X] = g(X\beta)\), for some function \(g\).
Linear regression is but a special case, \(E[Y|X] = X \beta\). This is what we will focus on today.
Least squares regression (otherwise termed ‚Äúordinary least squares‚Äù or ‚ÄúOLS‚Äù) refers to a particular method of estimating \(\beta\): minimize the sum of squared residuals.

